				<p class="paragraph--2">ISRM began evaluating the leading web application security tools in the market. The solution they would eventually choose needed to be able to assess thousands of applications annually and strong enough to handle significant demands for assessments as needs spike during busier periods. Also, the web application vulnerability assessment results needed to be accurate, with low rates of false positives and false negatives. “<b><i>We also required it to be easy to configure and use, so that our efforts could be streamlined. Comprehensive reporting was also essential,</i></b>” Mahdi says.</p>

